# Pokrovka, Bichursky District, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Pokrovka () is a rural locality (a selo) in Bichursky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 298 as of 2010. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Pokrovka is located 20&nbsp;km northwest of Bichura (the district's administrative centre) by road. Sudutuy is the nearest rural locality.
